# Privacy Policy for Form Accessibility Validator

## Data Collection
Form Accessibility Validator operates entirely within your browser and does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data or form content.

This extension does NOT collect:
- ❌ Personally identifiable information
- ❌ Health information
- ❌ Financial/payment information
- ❌ Authentication information
- ❌ Personal communications
- ❌ Location data
- ❌ Web history
- ❌ User activity tracking

## Permissions
- `activeTab`: Used to analyze forms on the current webpage
- `scripting`: Required to inject accessibility checking code
- `storage`: Used to save user preferences
- `windows`, `tabs`: Required for popup functionality

## Limited Website Content Access
The extension only accesses:
- ✅ Form elements on the current page
- ✅ HTML attributes of form elements
- ✅ CSS styles for contrast checking

## Data Usage
- All analysis is performed locally in the browser
- No data is stored externally
- No data is transmitted to servers
- Only user preferences are stored in chrome.storage

## Privacy Measures
- Forms are analyzed only when extension is activated
- No caching of form content
- No tracking or analytics
- No persistent storage of page content

## Updates
This privacy policy may be updated as the extension evolves. Users will be notified of significant changes.

## Contact
For privacy concerns, please open an issue on our GitHub repository.

